WorkItem.Description:
The intellisense for the first constructor argument does not show at first.

Example: 

```
class Test {
    /** Does something awesome.
    * @param {string} a The a value.
    * @param {string} b The b value.
    */
    constructor(a: string, b: string) { }
}

new Test(
```

Typing "new Test(" should give me BOTH the function description, and the first parameter description since there's only one function signature here. Currently, I have to actually start typing something before I even know what to type. ;)  (i.e. it does show when one starts typing)
